data.description: A package for evaluating bubble profile with a renomalization factor

evidence: "VacuumTunneling: A package for evaluating bubble profile with a renomalization factor in Mathematica" â€“ a domain-specific package users run inside Mathematica to perform tunneling calculations.

Usage is shown by loading and calling functions directly: `<<"VacuumTunneling`"` and `a = Tunneling[V[x], Z[x], x, tv, fv]`, indicating an end-user analysis tool rather than a lower-level library for other software.
Installation and use are described only via cloning/using the GitHub repo and loading the package in Mathematica; there is no mention of package registries, binaries, or containers.
